parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Key gets stuck in the ignition
unable to shut off the car or remove the key
engine stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Intermittent failure of displays on the instrument cluster
electrical fires
burning smell from the engine
loss of control while driving on wet pavements.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal and Brake Light Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of turn signals and brake lights can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: Turn signals and brake lights fail to function or malfunction
leading to near-misses or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump and Fuel System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump and fuel system can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalls or fails to start
fuel pump failure
fuel injection system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETS can cause the vehicle to lose control or shut down while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: ETS warning light illuminates
vehicle shuts down or loses control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of power windows can cause inconvenience and discomfort, especially in extreme weather conditions.
symptoms: Power windows fail to operate or malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cluster and odometer can cause inconvenience and make it difficult to track the vehicle's mileage.
symptoms: Odometer fails to function or displays incorrect mileage
cluster lights fail to illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake when applying the brakes, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Grinding noise when applying the brakes
vibration or shaking when braking
warped or thin rotors
premature wear of brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to loss of braking power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels to the floor
brake fluid leaks
corrosion on brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS system failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS light illuminates
loss of braking power
vibration or shaking when braking
grinding noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal issues can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels to the floor
brake pedal jerks back and forth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a popping sound
the timing chain gear
tensioner
and chain itself need to be replaced
and the engine sounds like it's about to fall out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine coolant system can cause overheating, engine damage, and accidents.
symptoms: The low coolant light comes on
coolant mixes with oil
the engine temperature gauge moves erratically
and the vehicle overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the fuel pump needs to be replaced
and the vehicle stalls without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including engine stalling, loss of power, and accidents.
symptoms: The engine check light stays on
the windshield wipers and automatic locks operate poorly
and the headlights and turn signals malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine performance issues can cause accidents, loss of power, and decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: The vehicle surges when cold
the engine stalls
and the vehicle accelerates on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oxygen sensor can cause engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
symptoms: The engine light illuminates
the oxygen sensor needs to be replaced
and the vehicle's fuel efficiency decreases.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dash cluster and gauges can cause confusion, decreased vehicle safety, and accidents.
symptoms: The dash cluster is inoperative
the gauges do not work
and the gas level indicator is inaccurate.
